SUMMARY:Square Dance
DESCRIPTION:A fun community dance event to meet new people\, hang with old friends\, and hear some great music. Advance tickets are strongly recommended. \nFamily Square Dance\, 5-6pm. Slower-paced\, for kiddos and their adults. Expect lots of easy moves and a rice-crispy styled cake walk. Featuring music by The Hodge Podge String Band. \nBig Square Dance\, 7-9pm. Faster-paced\, for anyone out for an adventure. Expect some easy moves\, some silly moves\, a good time for anyone\, and a cake walk “for adults”. Featuring music by The Lucky Strike Outs: Mike DeVito\, Hasee Ciaccio\, Vivian Leva\, and Aaron Tacke. The caller will be Nancy Mamlin for both dances. \nYou can choose to pay for a $10\, $15\, or $20 ticket based on your personal financial situation and ability to support the local arts scene. Kids under 12 are free! One ticket will get you into both dances. \nFullsteam will be selling beer at both dances and Queen Burger/Mellow Mushroom will be open if you wanna grab food beforehand.
URL:https://downtowndurham.com/event/square-dance/
LOCATION:Live at Bay 7\, 324 Blackwell St #700\, Durham\, 27701
CATEGORIES:Cultural,Dance,Date Night,Kid Friendly,LGBTQ,Live Performance
